    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1004"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1004">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 132.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram in cipher, which I translate as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>, <hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                1898.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister,
                                Madrid:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>This Government appreciates the courtesy intended in the visit of Spanish
                            ships to United States ports.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have officially informed the Spanish minister of foreign affairs of the receipt
                    of the above telegram, and have the honor to be,</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
